29/10/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Army cadets representing minority communities will be trained at military academies in Germany starting next year, according to an announcement on Friday (October 27th) by Defence Minister Lazar Elenovski and Army deputy chief Major General Adil Gazafer. 
Speaking at a news conference in Skopje, they said that an agreement on training was reached during their recent visit to Berlin. 
Currently, only 6% of Macedonian Army personnel are minorities. 
(Vecer, Vest - 28/10/06)
